<sections title="EclipseLink 2.3.0">

	<section class="title">
		<description>
			<h1>EclipseLink Indigo (2.3.0) Release</h1>
			<p>The EclipseLink 2.3 release focuses on increased developer
				flexibility allowing mapped objects to be extensible and multitenant
				to enable the development of SaaS solutions. </p>
		</description>
	</section>

	<section class="main" name="New and Noteworthy">

		<description>
			<h4>JPA: Object-Relational Mapping</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/DesignDocs/Extensibility">Extensible Entities</a>
					: Define and use extended mappings on-the-fly with database flex
					columns.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Development/Indigo/Multi-Tenancy">Multitenant</a>
					: SaaS enable your application with data from
					multiple tenants
					stored in the same table(s).
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>External Metadata Source</b>
					: Retrieve and use object-relational mapping from outside your
					application.
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>Extended Stored Procedure and PL/SQL Support</b>
					: Leverage more of your existing database features through JPA.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h4>MOXy: XML Binding with JAXB and SDO</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Development/339371">Extensible Beans</a>
					: Add XML Bindings on-the-fly
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Development/339373">Multiple Binding Files</a>
					: Greater flexibility for complex domains
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>External Metadata Source</b>
					: Retrieve and use XML binding definitions from outside your
					application.
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>XPath Mapping with Predicates</b>
					: ...
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h4>DBWS: Database Web Services</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>Complex PL/SQL arguments for stored functions</li>
				<li>Handle overloaded Stored Procedure/Functions as WSDL operations
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h4>Examples</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Examples/MySports">
						<b>MySports Example</b>
						: New example showing new 2.3 feature set
					</a>
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h4>Implement Standards</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>
					JPA 2.0 (
					<a href="http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=317">JSR 317</a>
					)
				</li>
				<li>
					JAXB 2.2 (
					<a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=222">JSR 222</a>
					)
				</li>
				<li>
					SDO 2.1.1(
					<a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=235">JSR 235</a>
					)
				</li>
			</ul>
		</description>

	</section>

